==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spongiae
<hw>Spon"gi*ae</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ocr⟧n"j⟦icr⟧*⟦emac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sponge</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
grand division of the animal kingdom which includes the sponges; --
called also <altname>Spongida</altname>, <altname>Spongiaria</altname>,
<altname>Spongiozoa</altname>, and
<altname>Porifera</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In the Spongiae, the soft sarcode of the body is usually
supported by a skeleton consisting of horny fibers, or of siliceous or
calcareous spicules. The common sponges contain larger and smaller
cavities and canals, and numerous small ampullae which are lined with
ciliated cells capable of taking in solid food. The outer surface
usually has minute pores through which water enters, and large openings
for its exit. Sponges produce eggs and spermatozoa, and the egg when
fertilized undergoes segmentation to form a ciliated embryo.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spongida</ent>⟦br⟧
